gujarati.source:
Here is a summarization of the couplet in English:

The heart beats fast, the throat gets choked with emotions, and love makes one forget all shame; 
Eyes become wet with tears, and the tender touch of someone's hand brings solace.

I've understood the Gujarati couplet as: 

"I have accumulated wisdom, but found it in vain; 
This is my way of living, as decreed by the great ruler of the universe."

I'll summarize this Gujarati couplet in English:

As I possess, I maintain happiness and unhappiness within myself; 
And I know the truth, without doubt or suspicion in my heart.
